Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.34,0:00:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor Agasa and Haibara went to attend an invention conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.93,0:00:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On their way back, the Professor's car broke down...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.64,0:00:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he also dropped his wallet, leaving them unable to board the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.48,0:00:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, they were able to get a ride in a passing car...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there were bullet holes inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.74,0:00:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And traces of where blood had been wiped away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the glove compartment was also a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.28,0:00:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are these two people who said they\Nintend to visit the Mouri Detective Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could they be members of the Black Organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.83,0:00:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After getting Haibara's call...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.96,0:00:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I headed toward the drive-in diner where the four of them were.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the suspicious couple who were waiting outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.64,0:00:46.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Were from the Nagano police - Inspector Yamato Kansuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.64,0:00:46.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yamato Kansuke (35)\NNagano Prefecture Police Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.57,0:00:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}And Detective Uehara Yui.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.65,0:00:48.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Uehara Yui (29)\NNagano Prefecture Police Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.18,0:00:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, talk about a huge false alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.64,0:00:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But these two...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.02,0:00:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what is it they're doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.71,0:00:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is magic, attack the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.73,0:01:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On Saturday nights, be sure to click on Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.35,0:01:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A new character from Nagano â€” Inspector Koumei.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.57,0:01:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Together well unravel the mystery of the Red Wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.41,0:01:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.08,0:01:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.95,0:01:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.98,0:02:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.27,0:02:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened in Nagano?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely you didn't come all this way just to give us botamochi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.94,0:03:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a case we can't solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we came to borrow your wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.36,0:03:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bloody...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.32,0:03:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery of the "Red Wall."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.38,0:03:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there really no roads smoother than this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think I, the famous detective Mouri\NKorogou, had to hear you guys out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.64,0:03:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And come all the way to Nagano to assist\Nyou on this murder investigation of yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that this kept me from eating any of that botamochi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.23,0:03:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.90,0:03:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the shortcut, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.61,0:03:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it about time you told us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What this bloody Red Wall mystery is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.87,0:03:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the wall was dyed deep red with\Nhuman blood, and is somewhere in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.66,0:04:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.25,0:04:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Bloody" was only Kan-chan's talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.00,0:04:04.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.71,0:04:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop it right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.59,0:04:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Preconceptions will interfere with your deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.89,0:04:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We wanted you to look at the scene yourself;\Nthat's why we bothered to escort you from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.39,0:04:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Uehara...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.39,0:04:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm technically your superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.73,0:04:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop calling me "Kan-chan."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato Kansuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, it'd be nice if you at least told\Nus where we're headed, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.03,0:04:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To an old mansion built in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.20,0:04:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One called the "Mansion of Hope."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mansion of Hope," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a charming name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only known by that name until three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.92,0:04:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, three years ago there was a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose miserable body was found\Nin the storage room of that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:05:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, the locals gave it a new name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of "Hope"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.31,0:05:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's now the "Mansion of Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mansion of Death...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.99,0:05:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's become quite old, but it's still a splendid house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.83,0:05:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because it was a villa owned by someone rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that Inspector Yamato is seeking help from Uncle Kogorou...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.05,0:05:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like him, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone he vowed not to lose to is also\Nparticipating in this investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.14,0:05:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That "someone" is also a police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But unlike us detectives with the Nagano\Nprefecture police headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.32,0:05:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a detective with this area's\Nlocal police station, the Arano police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.45,0:05:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he's the local detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would a headquarters detective compete with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.99,0:06:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be honest, that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.91,0:06:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a classmate of Kan-chan's since elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.04,0:06:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like they competed with each other in whatever they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although he graduated with honors from the\Nlaw department of Touto University...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.09,0:06:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't take the career test and went into the\Nprefectural police headquarters as a non-career, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of a case, this oddball\Ntransferred to the local station in Arano.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.68,0:06:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means, they were actually colleagues\Nat the same Nagano police headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.40,0:06:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also bears a tactician-like name, just like Kan-chan's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:32.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uehara!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.90,0:06:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.57,0:06:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the name "Yamato Kansuke"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds really close to Takeda Shingen's\Nfamous tactician, Yamamoto Kansuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan-chan has always been enraged by that rival of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's never beaten this rival, so please give him a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan-chan wasn't trying to get help from Detective Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems like it was actually from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.64,0:07:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain why they once called it the "Mansion of Hope."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\NWhen this mansion grew old, the\Nrich man who built it stopped using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.28,0:07:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He decided to handpick talented,\Nprospective young people without money...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.03,0:07:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And let them live here technically for free...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.20,0:07:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until they had fulfilled their dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.17,0:07:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as for that generous rich man\Nwho occasionally visited this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.34,0:07:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon after he settled to give this mansion\Nto those people, he died of illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.72,0:07:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And most of those people, after two or three years,\Nmoved out of this house to live on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since five or six years ago, the only ones still\Nliving in this house were a married couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.11,0:07:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uehara.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show them the photos of the people who were living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:07:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was these six people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.74,0:08:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first photo you're looking at...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.99,0:08:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is an illustrator, Akashi Shuusaku-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, an actor, Midorikawa Naoki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.59,0:08:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next one is a novelist, Kobashi Aoi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.05,0:08:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fashion designer, Yamabuki Shouji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.51,0:08:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Computer graphic creator, Momose Takuto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.93,0:08:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last is a musician, Naoki Shirou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.31,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I may have heard those names somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe not, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.65,0:08:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed something a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.37,0:08:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are traces of a torn paper that\Nhad once been glued to this door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.33,0:08:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right - this door has a similar outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:08:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think those...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.63,0:08:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were colors they used for identification, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Colors?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet they stuck colored paper on\Nthe doors to distinguish their rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since all six people have colors in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their names are on the photos...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no one has a name with the kanji of a color...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.90,0:09:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not the kanji, it's the pronunciation!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,**********\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.36,0:09:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H1F2CC9&)}Aka{\r}shi Shuusaku-san is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.53,0:09:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H1F2CC9&)}Red{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H687B2E&}Midori{\r}kawa Naoki-san is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.49,0:09:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H687B2E&}Green{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.33,0:09:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kobashi {\c&HEED194&}Aoi{\r}-san is {\c&HEED194&}blue{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.70,0:09:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And {\c&H14D2F8&}Yamabuki {\r}Shouji-san is {\c&H14D2F8&}golden yellow{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.58,0:09:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFE9DFE&}Momo{\r}se Takuto-san is {\c&HFE9DFE&}pink{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Naoki {\3c&HF5F5F8&\bord0.1\blur20\}Shiro{\r}u-san is... {\3c&HF5F5F8&\bord0.1\blur20\}white{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.17,0:09:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All six people have colors in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.67,0:09:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good find, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.01,0:09:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The six people also...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.68,0:09:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Used colors to distinguish their own names as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.39,0:09:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an old cooking duty list we found in the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:10:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's written on it isn't their names, but their colors in kanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm assuming...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.65,0:10:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They even called one another by color instead of by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.53,0:10:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the room where the body was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.00,0:10:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.42,0:10:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with those cardboard boxes stacked on that cart?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're only books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.01,0:10:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's a lot of them, which makes them heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door swings outwards, and was blocked by the cart at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.23,0:10:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who was inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.35,0:10:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't get out and ended up dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that room is the rumored...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.86,0:10:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.11,0:10:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had already starved to death and lost a lot of weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.99,0:10:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this disgusting...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room with the Red Wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.36,0:10:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.79,0:10:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Human blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.75,0:11:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.42,0:11:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The nozzle of the spray can lying on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.09,0:11:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has the same red color as what's on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.14,0:11:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... what are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.56,0:11:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These black and white chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.39,0:11:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like they've been purposely painted and nailed to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.98,0:11:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body was upright on the white chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.32,0:11:26.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A message left by the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.82,0:11:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bug had been installed and was still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.25,0:11:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bug?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit eavesdropped on this room and\Nchecked on the victim's vitals through the sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.67,0:11:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should the sounds stop, the culprit would've\Ncome to this room to confirm the victim's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.22,0:11:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then that they'd retrieve the bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since the bug was still here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.44,0:11:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was locked in here and the culprit never returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.86,0:12:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red wall, as well as the black and white chairs, are in fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.53,0:12:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Left by the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.05,0:12:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dying message!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.80,0:12:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meaning of this red wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.22,0:12:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured it out yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.26,0:12:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The message is "red."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.26,0:12:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person whose name contains "red"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.14,0:12:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Akashi guy is the culprit, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.77,0:12:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shriveled-up victim in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.90,0:12:47.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that Akashi Shuusaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.57,0:12:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About Akashi Shuusaku's wife, Kobashi Aoi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her surname was changed to Akashi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.12,0:13:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years ago, she died in the storage room of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, she was murdered too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, her heart had always been weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.17,0:13:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was looking for something in the storage room\Nwhen she had a heart attack, and died like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.22,0:13:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her husband Shuusaku-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.68,0:13:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was completing his work in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he finally discovered his wife lying on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half a day already passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.56,0:13:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.19,0:13:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "aka" doesn't mean the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aka...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aka no...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.78,0:13:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! The culprit was a stranger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.87,0:13:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't bring you here from Tokyo to listen\Nto you pulling answers out of your -
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Attempting to meet a worthy man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without taking the proper course...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is as if inviting him to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.34,0:13:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet barring the gate against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.01,0:13:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't merely summon the famous detective here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead personally escorted him here, which is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.90,0:14:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your demeanor toward Detective Mouri just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was insolently rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As an old acquaintance of yours, I can only feel embarrassment...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.62,0:14:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kansuke-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.28,0:14:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why the hell're you here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.37,0:14:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Local cops should stay out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This territory falls under the jurisdiction of the Arano police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.33,0:14:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I cannot merely stand down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.50,0:14:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop talking nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.17,0:14:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.51,0:14:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Attempting to eat a woolly man"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.05,0:14:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not "attempting to eat a woolly man"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.72,0:14:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei was from the Three Kingdoms era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.43,0:14:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to recruit a famous sage as his tactician...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He decided to meet him personally by saying the following:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.31,0:14:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Attempting to meat a worthy man without taking the proper course...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Is as if inviting him to come yet barring the gate against him."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.32,0:14:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.36,0:15:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm trying to recruit a famous man, but if I summoned\Nhim instead of properly paying him a visit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.62,0:15:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It will appear as if I don't really wish for him\Nto come and have closed the gate on him."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.21,0:15:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After saying that, Liu Bei even took\Nthe effort and paid him three visits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you didn't know a thing about Fuurinkazan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.63,0:15:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you so familiar with the Three Kingdoms?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.51,0:15:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.64,0:15:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In regards to the mystery bequeathed to this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't limited to this red wall nor the white and black chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sealed window was broken from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through that opening, items such as tubes of paint, sprays...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.57,0:15:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And art supplies with colors were all thrown out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.95,0:15:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one that remained in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.37,0:15:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this red can of spray paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.25,0:15:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim bit into his own finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.21,0:15:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And used the blood to sign his name upon the edge of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.84,0:15:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To properly evaluate these clues...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.34,0:16:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's logical to seek the assessment of a prominent detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tactician...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.89,0:16:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three visits?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.69,0:16:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, that would be done in my presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.73,0:16:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that, when the body was initially found...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:16.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drawing utensils were scattered outside the mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.99,0:16:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it was those that caught my eye as I happened to pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.53,0:16:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me that tactician is the famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he always held a feather fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.83,0:16:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you may be from the headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.54,0:16:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That degree of disrespect toward me is unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.84,0:16:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.80,0:16:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay as long as you'd like, even until you drop dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.01,0:16:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shokatsuryou...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ko-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.73,0:16:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have yet to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}My surname is Morosuhi...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}And my name is Takaaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.11,0:16:56.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\be5\fad(250,0)}Morofushi Takaaki (35)\N{\fs13}Nagano Prefecture Arano Station Inspector
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.44,0:17:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People refer to me by the Chinese pronounciation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Koumei."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.36,0:17:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the future, please remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.70,0:17:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of Shokatsuryou Koumei...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&HD9A159&\fs13\be2}shokatsu\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\N{\r}He's "Local Detective Koumei," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorou-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.01,0:17:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This wall sprayed with red paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.18,0:17:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's bloody signature at the bottom...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.93,0:17:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sealed window being broken from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.14,0:17:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While painting materials were thrown outside through the opening...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.15,0:17:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.32,0:17:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These two chairs which were painted white\Nand black and nailed down to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man who was locked up in this room and starved to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.20,0:17:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it he wanted to tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.24,0:17:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're asking me if I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.58,0:17:58.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, this can't be solved with ease even with\Nthe wits of a reputable detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.42,0:18:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Red, white, and black!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.26,0:18:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to use those three colors to tell us something, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.18,0:18:10.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because all the other colors were thrown out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this young boy is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.73,0:18:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's staying at Sleeping Kogorou's detective agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.69,0:18:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A brat named Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.49,0:18:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About these boxes stacked on that cart that was blocking the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.45,0:18:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said there were books inside, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were Aoi-san's books.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.67,0:18:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, we mentioned her earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.67,0:18:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the wife of the man who starved to\Ndeath in this room - Akashi Shuusaku-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years ago, she died of illness in the storage\Nroom - her maiden name was Kobashi Aoi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The books from the shelves in her room were removed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put in those cardboard boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had a lot of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a novelist, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.61,0:19:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe Aoi-san's siblings did this to\Nhold the victim responsible for her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.74,0:19:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since, when Aoi-san had a heart attack in the storage room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.41,0:19:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shuusaku-san was busy drawing and\Ndidn't find her until half a day later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.96,0:19:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, she had no siblings...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aoi-san was an only child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And both of her parents died early...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.67,0:19:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, those who used to live with these two people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.34,0:19:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those four men are suspicious, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, the fact that there were many books in Aoi-san's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.73,0:19:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that the door opens outward requires prior knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.19,0:19:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, the culprit wouldn't think of placing a\Ncart filled with boxes of books to block the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.99,0:19:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might be the actor, Midorikawa Naoki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fashion designer, Yamabuki Shouji-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The CG creator, Momose Takuto-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or the musician, Naoki Shirou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very likely to be one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.59,0:20:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Uncle Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.60,0:20:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.85,0:20:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Up to this point, your deduction has been the same as ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.27,0:20:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you didn't speak it out loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.32,0:20:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is because you believe a deduction of this level need not be said, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.53,0:20:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.74,0:20:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.26,0:20:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.79,0:20:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll confirm that myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kan-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.01,0:20:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.29,0:20:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.79,0:20:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fingerprints on the doorknob inside the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the fingerprints on the red spray paint can...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.55,0:20:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that they had belonged to the victim, Akashi Shuusaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.39,0:20:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Koumei!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're from your subordinate who was with\Nyou when you found the body, or so I heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:09.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, we're calling that detective back\Nto the station to begin questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.11,0:21:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I beg your people not to be too hard on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.37,0:21:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that he only recently made detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.37,0:21:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have panicked upon seeing a body for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.66,0:21:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could have led to him aimlessly feeling around the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the people who found the body\Nwere you and that novice detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.84,0:21:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.01,0:21:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were in the car after having just finished investigating a case...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked him to drive me to this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.35,0:21:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to place some flowers in front of the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.66,0:21:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flowers?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.73,0:21:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We forgot to mention it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.03,0:21:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi and Inspector Yamato...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.95,0:21:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were classmates of that Aoi-san who\Ndied in the storage room three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.08,0:21:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Classmates?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.58,0:22:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The classmate of Kobashi Aoi-san who died in\Nthis mansion's storage room three years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That inspector being the primary discoverer\Nof Akashi Shuusaku-san's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.26,0:22:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it a mere coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.59,0:22:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.63,0:22:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akashi-san left us a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.80,0:22:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wall that was covered in red spray paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.18,0:22:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two chairs that were painted white\Nand black, and nailed to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it Akashi-san was trying to tell us with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.90,0:22:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Red Wall's Mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.73,0:22:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the culprit who let Akashi-san starve to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.49,0:22:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to reveal the culprit's identity in due course!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's as improbable as...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.95,0:24:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finding bamboo shoots in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.95,0:24:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was indeed someone strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, about Aoi-san, what kind of person was she?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.21,0:24:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a Red Wall again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.92,0:24:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind," is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.05,0:24:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as we found the key person to solving this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.01,0:24:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've had him murdered under our own watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.58,0:24:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.97,0:24:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chess
